1. PREAMBLE
This License is founded on the principle that knowledge and software are 
common goods. It aims to empower students, educators, and independent 
creators while ensuring that corporate interests do not enclose the 
commons or profit from the uncompensated labor of the community.

2. DEFINITIONS
"Work" refers to the shmenu software and all associated files.
"Derivative Work" refers to any software that includes, modifies, or 
links to the Work.
"Commercial Use" refers to any use by a for-profit entity or any use 
intended for commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

3. GRANT OF RIGHTS
The Author hereby grants a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license 
to individuals, self-organized learning groups, and non-profit educational 
institutions to:
    a) Use, study, and execute the Work for any non-commercial purpose.
    b) Modify, extend, and adapt the Work to suit their educational needs.
    c) Redistribute the Work or Derivative Works, provided they remain 
       under this exact License.

4. THE "OPEN ECOSYSTEM" OBLIGATION (STRICT COPYLEFT)
To ensure the Work contributes to the global pool of knowledge:
    a) Any project that incorporates the Work MUST be made public.
    b) The source code of any Derivative Work MUST be provided openly.
    c) You may NOT apply any technical measures (DRM) or legal terms 
       that restrict others from exercising the rights granted herein.

5. NON-COMMERCIAL & ANTI-EXPLOITATION CLAUSE
The Work is a gift to humanity, not a resource for capital extraction.
    a) Direct or indirect commercial exploitation is prohibited.
    b) Entities with a primary goal of profit-making must obtain 
       explicit written permission and negotiate a separate agreement.
    c) This restriction is waived for students using the Work for 
       personal portfolios or school-related employment applications.

6. EDUCATIONAL PRECEDENCE
This License explicitly encourages the use of the Work in classrooms, 
coding clubs, and academic research. The Author waives all notice 
requirements for students: you are free to learn and build.

7. DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTY
THE WORK IS PROVIDED "AS IS". THE AUTHOR SHALL NOT BE HELD LIABLE FOR 
ANY DAMAGES ARISING FROM THE USE OF THIS SOFTWARE.
